Privacy Policy for Android Game

Last updated: 2024-Dec-01

ApmeM ("We" or "Our Company") has developed the mobile game GodotTemplate ("the Game"). This Privacy Policy explains what data we collect, how it is used, and how it is protected.

1. Data Collection and Usage
We respect your privacy and are committed to minimizing data collection. The Game does not collect, store, or share any personal user data.

2. Third-Party Services
The Game uses Google Play Services, provided by Google LLC, to ensure proper functioning of the following features:

Google Play authentication.
Storing achievements and leaderboards.
Managing in-app purchases.
For more information about Googleâ€™s data practices, please refer to the Google Privacy Policy.

3. Data Security
We do not collect personal data, so there are no data security risks related to user information in the Game. However, third-party services like Google Play Services manage their own data protection policies.

4. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted within the Game or on our official website. Please review this Policy periodically for updates.

